HEADWORD: Wickered
<hw>Wick"ered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made of, secured by,
or covered with, wickers or wickerwork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ships of light timber, <qex>wickered</qex> with osier between, and
covered over with leather.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wickerwork</ent>⟦br⟧
